cs.NI, cs.CR, cs.DC, cs.SY, cs.DS 

Reasoning: 
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is the most likely category as the paper discusses the use of blockchain for managing connectivity in the Internet of Vehicles. 
- cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) is also likely as the paper discusses the safety and reliability of the blockchain mechanism. 
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is relevant as the proposed approach involves distributed clustering to optimize the number of transactions. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is relevant as the proposed approach involves controlling the number of transactions to manage energy demands. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is relevant as the paper discusses the number of transactions required to update ledgers and proposes an efficient model to reduce this number.
